20/07/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- The government announced on Tuesday (19 July) that it has decided to purchase 30 F-16 fighter planes from Lockheed Martin.
The order, which could be worth up to 1.1 billion euros, includes an option to acquire another 10 aircraft, Foreign Minister Spilios Spiliotopoulos said.
The final price is yet to be negotiated.
(FT - 20/07/05)
